# Cortex AI Tech - Frontend Notes
## 5th Lecture (29-08-2024)
### background-color
Sets the background color of an element.
```
background-color: red;
```
### color
Sets the color of text.
```
color: blue;
```
### text-align
Aligns text within an element.
```
text-align: center;
```
## Border Properties
###  border-width

Sets the width of an element's border.
```
border-width: 2px;
```
### border-style
Sets the style of an element's border.
```
border-style: solid;
```
### border-color
Sets the style of an element's border.
```
border-color: black;
```
### border (shorthand property)
Sets all four borders of an element at once.
```
border: 2px solid black;
```
### border radius
Rounds the corners of an element's border.
```
border-radius: 10px;
```
## Margin
### Sets the space around an element.
```
margin: 10px;
```

## Padding
### Sets the space between an element's content and its border.

```
padding: 10px;
```
## Box Model
### Defines how elements are sized and positioned.
### Components:
* content
* padding
* border
* margin
### Properties
* width
* height

## box-sizing: border-box
### Changes how the width and height of an element are calculated.
### By default, width and height only include the content box.
### With box-sizing : border-box, width and height include the content, padding, and border
